reviews.review_text: It is just a  state of mind... I had a  blast at this run and this first show has many highlights.The first set is upbeat focused and long.Set II has some vocal miscues during HC Sunshine & Ship of Fools, much less, and Jerry's playing is inspiring, as is the band.Samson, Way to go and Saint are all very good. Post drums has the last Comes A Time, which many of us waited for since Atlanta, and Jerry  delivers an inspired and hopeful version with a sweet solo and strong vocals and some great playing by Phil too. The set ends strong and the Rain is the second highlight of the night, maybe the song that represents 1994 the best. We should have a  nicer sounding board of this show, it deserves it.
Woo hoo Sound quality is terrific! Broken Arrow was awesome, gave me goose bumps! Didnt mind the encore either, not a huge Beatles fan but that was nice...
Last Comes A Time 5 stars for the last comes a time

10-9-94 Excellent sound as per usual with Charlie transfers. Good show for this era. I mean it doesn't make me forget about the incredible shows from the older era but God damnit it's still the Grateful Dead.

Wonky recording. Phasey after Big River The sound is excellent from Spoonful until about halfway through Big River, when it takes a real phasey turn and sounds like the 'fake live Benny and the Jets' effect on everything. It really ruins it for me. Some might like it as it does give a live feel. It just washes out the detail too much for me. Frail sounding Jerry but heartfelt performance. Last comes a Time a great little gold tooth.
